dash to dock
	Run the following:
		sudo mv /usr/share/gnome-shell/extensions/ubuntu-dock@ubuntu.com{,.bak}
		Press ALT + F2 and type r in the input.


dual boot windows time
	timedatectl set-local-rtc 1


useful gnome extensions
	dash to dock
		A dock for the Gnome Shell. This extension moves the dash out of the overview transforming it in a dock for an easier launching of applications and a faster switching between windows and desktops. Side and bottom placement options are available.

	no screen blank
		Disable blanking the screen after showing the lock screen

	Quick Close in Overview
		Close windows with a button click (the middle one by default) when in overview mode

	WindowOverlay Icons
		Add application icons to window overview
